text: Kaukolikai is a village in Lithuania. It is located in the Skuodas District Municipality. According to the 2011 census, the village had 285 residents. The village is the hometown of Lithuanian singer Mia. ==External links== *Website of the Juozo alus brewery complex (in Lithuanian, English, German, Latvian and Russian) ==References== Category:Villages in Klaipėda County
